<TITLE> Bangladesh signs revised OIC charter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 19 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh has signed the revised charter of the Organisation of Islamic Conference, the foreign ministry said in a statement Thursday. Foreign secretary Md Touhid Hossain signed the revised charter in the presence of the representatives of 57 member countries attending the 35th council of foreign ministers meeting in Kampala. The three-day event that started on June 18 was inaugurated by Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni at a ceremony held at Munyonyo Commonwealth Resort. Saudi Arabia, Turkey, Malaysia and Indonesia are the other countries to approve the revised charter at the Kampala summit. The OIC at its 11th Islamic summit in Dakar, the capital of Senegal, adopted the revised charter. Bangladesh and other countries did not approve the charter immediately. bdn
